{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluations of four predictive models-Artificial Neural Network (ANN), Generalized Linear Model (GLM), Ground Penetrating Radar (GPR), and Support Vector Machine Regression (SVR)-show reductions in verification time with high accuracy.",
    "The methodology involves training predictive models with simulator-generated data and using these models to predict execution times during the GA-evolution process, making WCET estimation more efficient.In conclusion, the evolving landscape of WCET analysis has seen significant advancements through innovative methods such as ML integration, hybrid techniques, and dynamic analysis approaches.",
    "These developments address the challenges posed by complex modern hardware architectures, enhancing the precision and reliability of WCET estimates in real-time systems.This thesis provides a comparative analysis of two widely utilized algorithms for WCET estimation: GAs and RL.",
    "Our method that utilizes RL has distinct advantages over those that use ML for determining WCET.",
    "Despite their advantages, ML-based WCET methods confront several challenges, such as data dependency and collection, where the efficacy of ML models is dependent on the availability of diverse and representative datasets, which can be challenging to collect in practice [20]."
  ]
}